      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add reset family carryover summaries",
        "body": "## Behavior or issue addressed\n\nDepends on #90239.\n\nWhen a session has been reset/rotated, the active transcript can be clean while the previous reset archive still contains the latest compaction summary. The next embedded-agent prompt therefore starts without the carryover context unless the model/tool explicitly asks for family history.\n\nThis change reuses the session-family transcript resolver from #90239 and injects the latest reset-archive compaction summary into embedded-agent prompt context before the LLM boundary, but only when the active context does not already contain a compaction summary.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Move the #90239 family/reset transcript target resolver into a shared gateway helper.\n- Keep `chat.history(includeFamily)` on the shared resolver.\n- Pass the current session store path/entry into embedded-agent attempts.\n- Add a prompt-context transform that prepends one `compactionSummary` from reset ancestor transcripts.\n- Skip injection when the active session already has a compaction summary.\n- Cap family transcript read targets before reading files; ancestor targets stop at the cap while current-session targets remain available.\n- Rebased onto current `origin/main` and preserved the newer transcript-reader seam plus same-session reset fallback.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** When the active post-reset session has no compaction summary but reset-family transcripts have persisted compaction rows, the embedded-agent prompt context should carry the active reset-family summary forward exactly once before the LLM boundary without reading unowned reset archives or every retained lineage target.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local upstream checkout at `/home/clever/.openclaw/workspace/github/openclaw` on branch `pr-90259`, current head `cda0a9633c`, using real TypeScript source modules and temporary on-disk OpenClaw-like session stores/transcripts under `/tmp`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n\n1. Created a temporary on-disk session store where `main` points at a clean active session and `usageFamilySessionIds` contains 35 ancestor sessions plus the current session.\n2. Wrote real JSONL transcript files with compaction rows for each ancestor and an active-current compaction row that must be skipped by carryover.\n3. Invoked `resolveSessionFamilyTranscriptReadTargets`, `resolveSessionFamilyCarryoverSummary`, and `installSessionFamilyCarryoverContextTransform` from the branch source with `node --import tsx`, outside Vitest.\n4. Applied the transform to the prompt messages that would be handed to the model boundary and applied it a second time to prove idempotence.\n5. Re-ran focused Gateway/carryover tests plus prompt snapshots, TypeScript, and whitespace checks after rebasing onto current main.\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\nTerminal capture from current head:\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'SMOKE'\n# smoke creates /tmp/openclaw-family-proof-* transcripts, resolves carryover,\n# installs the prompt transform, and applies it to pre-LLM messages\nSMOKE\n{\n  \"targetCount\": 31,\n  \"currentTargetPresent\": true,\n  \"skippedBeyondCap\": true,\n  \"promptRolesBeforeLlm\": [\n    \"compactionSummary\",\n    \"user\"\n  ],\n  \"compactionSummaryCount\": 1,\n  \"idempotentRoles\": [\n    \"compactionSummary\",\n    \"user\"\n  ],\n  \"carryoverSummary\": \"Capped carryover 29\",\n  \"carryoverTokensBefore\": 1029\n}\n\n$ npm run test -- src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat-b.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-family-carryover.test.ts\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  82 passed (82)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  6 passed (6)\n\n$ npm run prompt:snapshots:check\nPrompt snapshots are current (7 files).\n\n$ npm run tsgo:test:src\n# passed\n\n$ git diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n\n- The shared resolver stops before reading the whole 35-ancestor lineage: it returns 31 targets and keeps the current active target.\n- Ancestor 30 and later are not read before final history/prompt budgets (`skippedBeyondCap: true`).\n- Prompt carryover skips the active current compaction row and selects the latest compaction inside the capped family window, `Capped carryover 29`.\n- The installed prompt transform produces exactly one carryover summary immediately before the model boundary: `promptRolesBeforeLlm` is `[\"compactionSummary\", \"user\"]` and `compactionSummaryCount` is `1`.\n- Applying the transform again keeps the same roles, proving the carryover is not duplicated.\n- Gateway `chat.history(includeFamily)` has focused coverage for the same cap behavior and still preserves current-session content.\n\n**Implementation safety proof added in this head:**\n\n- Family history reuses `resolveSessionTranscriptResetArchiveCandidatesAsync`, the existing bounded/cached/header-checked reset archive resolver.\n- The family target cap is enforced in `resolveSessionFamilyTranscriptReadTargets`, so it applies to both Gateway `chat.history(includeFamily)` and embedded prompt carryover before transcript reads begin.\n- The cap reserves room for current-session targets so long ancestor lineages do not hide current context.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full end-to-end Telegram reset turn against a live gateway was not run locally. The current-head smoke, regressions, and tests exercise the real shared resolver, prompt transform, and embedded carryover path against real on-disk session artifacts.\n## Current head addendum: `cda0a9633c`\n\nClawSweeper findings from the `e5b25e79cb` review are addressed in the current head:\n\n- `resolveSessionFamilyTranscriptReadTargets` now reserves one target slot for the current active transcript when current reset archives exist, so capped ancestor/reset archives cannot displace active post-reset context.\n- Embedded `chat.history(includeFamily)` now uses the shared family resolver, so `sessions_history` with `includeFamily`/`resetAncestors` has parity in embedded mode instead of exposing a flag that the embedded gateway ignores.\n- Added regression coverage for capped ancestors plus current reset archives and for embedded family history resolving ancestor reset archives.\n\nValidation on `cda0a9633c`:\n\n```text\n$ npm run test -- src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat-b.test.ts src/agents/tools/embedded-gateway-stub.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-family-carryover.test.ts\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  82 passed (82)\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  16 passed (16)\n\n$ npm run prompt:snapshots:check\nPrompt snapshots are current (7 files).\n\n$ npm run tsgo:test:src\n# passed\n\n$ git diff --check\n# no output\n```",
        "branch": "fix/session-carryover-summary",
